packageJSON.name: keysave
packageJSON.description: A cross platform KeySAV based on GitHub Electron for all your Generation VI Pokémon decryption needs.

releases.name: 1.4.0 - TEA for Generation 7!
releases.body:
**If the automatic update does not work for you, please get the new version manually from [here](https://github.com/Cu3PO42/KeySAVe/releases/latest). The update does not work on most Windows 7 installations currently!**

### Added
- TEA Support for Generation 7! (#141)
- Add a Chinese localization for everything but Generation 6 form names

### Fixed
- Allow opening of raw Generation 7 box files, this time really (#158)
- Fixed the display of the localization of the beast ball when using Handlebars formatting

**If the automatic update does not work for you, please get the new version manually from [here](https://github.com/Cu3PO42/KeySAVe/releases/latest). The update does not work on most Windows 7 installations currently!**

### Changed
- Allow opening of raw Generation 7 box files (#158)
- Allow easy access to Handlebars methods from the `eval` helper
- Added sprites for Generation 7 Pokémon and forms, thanks @MalikTH! (#157)
- Changed the handling of TIDs in the Handlebars formatter. `tid6` now always maps to a 5-digit TID, whereas `tid` maps to whatever the game would display. `tid7` now displays 'N/A' on Pokémon that are from Generation 6 or earlier games, but remains otherwise unchanged.
- Added a new default format for TSVs that does not include the SID, but will choose the appropriate TID depending on game of origin. The old format is available as 'TID (Legacy)'.

### Fixed
- Fixed the localizations of Generation 7 forms. Thanks @Bobblybook! (Cu3PO42/KeySAVCoreJS#11)
- Pokémon from Generation 7 Pokémon are now dumped in the correct format
- Fixed the formatting of Generation 7 markings
- Properly clear 'in-progress' state upon application reboot (#145)
- Only copy Pokémon to the clipboard that match the filters

releases.name: 1.3.1 - Lots of SuMo bug fixes!
releases.body:
**If the automatic update fails for you, you can download the latest version manually from [here](https://github.com/Cu3PO42/KeySAVe/releases/latest).**

### Fixed
- Fixed an issue in the Reddit formatter that caused any attempt to copy the output to clipboard or save it to fail (#139)
- Fixed a bug that caused Pokémon with National Dex IDs of 750 or greater not to show up (#143)
- Fixed some typos (#142)
- Fixed a bug that caused import of KeySAV2 keys to fail (#148)
- Made the checks on battle video keys less strict, which means you should now be able to break keys even if the opponent doesn't do the procedure (#146)
- All states that rely on operations finishing are now cleared on a restart. If you start a scan for KeySAV2 keys and quit the app, the loading circle will be gone (#145)
- Fixed a bug that caused TEA trade dumps to fail in Generation 6 games (#150)

releases.name: KeySAVe 1.3.0 - Preliminary SuMo support!
releases.body:
### Added
- Added support for Pokémon Sun and Moon.

### Changed
- All application state is now persisted between sessions.
- Show a form name whenever one is available, even if the form id is 0.

### Fixed
- Only Pokémon that satisfy the filters are exported (#136).
- All Vivillon and Unown forms show the correct sprites (#133).

### Changed
- Changed the way filtering is handled to improve performance. #83
- Changed the location of the log file to `%APPDATA%/keysave/keysave.log` (Windows), `~/.config/keysave/keysave.log` (Linux), `~/Library/Application Support/keysave/keysave.log` (macOS).
- Add file type filters to the open dialogs. #51

### Fixed
- Added sprites for Pokéball Vivillon to pretty formatter. This fixes a bug where no Pokémon would be shown at all. #128

### Fixes
- Fix sprites of alternate forms not being shown in all cases.
- Add missing sprites for forms with a form number greater 8. #118
- Fix the nasty bug that caused TEA not to work if 'dump trade' was clicked too early. #119 
- Add the missing `notOTFriendship` and `notOTAffection` fields. #121 
- Ignore possibly corrupted Pokémon in key breaking sequence. #116 
- Always persist all data properly on shutdown. #117

### Fixed
- Fixed a race condition that would cause the main window not to show in a lot of cases.

*\* THIS RELEASE HAS A MAJOR ISSUE: PLEASE USE 1.2.1 INSTEAD**

### Added
- Added TEA dumping: Can dump trades in progress using NTR CFW.
- Added logging. This will be helpful in debugging possible future issues.
- Save the SV filter in the config.

### Changed
- Hide the menubar by default on Windows and Linux. Press `Alt` to show it. (thanks @bulldog98!)

### Fixed
- Rewrite the updater entirely. This should fix some problems Windows users were experiencing.

### Fixed
- Fixed a bug that prevented all Handlebars formats from working.

### Changed
- TID and SID are now padded to 5 digits in Handlebars and Legacy formats. (#104)
- Change how form names are handled in the Legacy plugin. Instead of just showing the form names for certain Pokémon, show it whenever there is an alternate form.

### Fixed
- Use the proper ball name for the ball image helper in Handlebars. (#109)
- Fix a bug that would cause specific battle video slots and saves to not save their key and crash KeySAVe on some platforms. (#101)
- Fix a minor layout in the breaking tab. (#110)
- Fix the breaking result messages in some cases and add a new error when saving the key to disk fails.
- Fix a bug that would cause KeySAVe to become unresponsive when unknown helpers were used. (#107)

### Changed
- Slightly tweaked default formatting options to more closely resemble KeySAV2 defaults.
- Updated all dependencies.
- App is bundled as `asar` file. This means a slight increase in bundle size, but should resolve issues with path length on Windows and enable incremental updates in the future.

### Fixes
- Fix the updater (again).
- Interpret Handlebars box header as HTML.
- Fix the upper box filter. It now properly excludes all boxes above the selected number instead of including the next one as well.

### Added
- Added a Characteristic' helper for the Handlebars option.
- Added a lot of math helpers for Handlebars (modulo, binary operations).
- Added an eval helper for Handlebars. See the documentation for more information about these.

### Changed
- Instead of sliders for box selection there are now dropdown menus for performance reasons and to make an accurate selection easier.
- Changed how the alternate form Handlebars helper works. Instead of checking if the Pokémon is actually a non-standard form, it checks if the species has multiple forms and the current form has a special name.

### Fixed
- Fixed a bug that would mean only the first of the entered SVs in the filter was properly parsed.
- Fixed some scenarios in which the formatting options wouldn't update properly.
- Fixed custom formatting options not saving properly under some circumstances.
- Fixed Pokémon forms being displayed incorrectly.

This version is basically an entire rewrite of previous versions, as such a lot has changed

### Added
- Added a plugin system that allows for your own formatting plugins.
- Added a pretty output plugin.
- Display Markdown output like it will look on Reddit.
- Support for formatting strings from KeySAV2.
- Wrote a documentation.
- Added Handlebars dashbars helpers.
- Added a custom filter that allows you to execute arbitrary code.
- You can now open files by pressing Ctrl/Cmd+O

### Changed
- Improved key management (slots may unlock quicker).
- KeySAV2 installations are no longer searched for automatically, this is now a menu option.
- You can specify KeySAV2 installations manually, too.
- Improved overall responsiveness.

### Fixed
- Inability to use filters.
- Met and hatched date now display the month correctly.

releases.name: 1.0.0 - Release Candidate 1
releases.body:
This version is basically an entire rewrite of previous versions, as such a lot has changed

### Added
- Added a plugin system that allows for your own formatting plugins.
- Added a pretty output plugin.
- Display Markdown output like it will look on Reddit.
- Support for formatting strings from KeySAV2.
- Wrote a documentation.
- Added Handlebars dashbars helpers.
- Added a custom filter that allows you to execute arbitrary code.

### Changed
- Improved key management (slots may unlock quicker).
- KeySAV2 installations are no longer searched for automatically, this is now a menu option.
- You can specify KeySAV2 installations manually, too.
- Improved overall responsiveness.

### Fixed
- Inability to use filters.
- Met and hatched date now display the month correctly.

releases.name: 1.0.0 - Release Candidate 2
releases.body:
### Fixed
- Removed a superfluous `|` character in the Reddit output.
- Fixed the box filters not working.

### Fixed
- Fixed an issue with old style keys that would cause them to not work or be saved at all.
- Fixed the dialog being shown while scanning a folder never closing after the scan is complete.
- The same dialog can also not be closed manually while a scan is in progress anymore.

### Fixed
- Fixed a bug that would cause slots 1-6 in boxes 1 and 2 to never unlock properly with keys broken on 0.17.0. If you have created keys on 0.17.0 please delete them by going to `~/Library/Application Support/keysave/keys` on OS X, `%APPDATA%\keysave\keys` on Windows or `~/.config/keysave/keys` on Linux to delete the respective key file while KeySAVe is closed and create the key again. Sorry for the inconvenience!
- Fixed a bug with the updater that would cause an error message and the version number not to update. If you get this bug while updating, it is non-fatal! Your update will finish after you restart KeySAVe manually.

**DISCLAIMER: THE UPDATER IN 0.16.11 IS BROKEN UNFORTUNATELY. PLEASE UPDATE MANUALLY**

### Added
- Upon first start, KeySAVe will try to find keys from KeySAV2 installations.
- An opened file is watched for changes. I.e. if you change the file on disk, it will be reloaded.
- With all subsequent updates, the version number  of the applications on Mac and Windows will be updated.

### Changed
- Rewrote a lot of code to use new ECMAScript features.
- There is now only one dumping tab instead of two. It will open both battle videos and save files.
- Make the UI more responsive, by moving a lot of calculations to a second thread.
- Store keys in an OS specific application folder instead of `~/Documents/KeySAVe/data`.
- Keys are now stored automatically when they are created.
- When you export Pokémon, you will be asked for a folder to change the Pokémon to.
- When you backup a save file or battle video you will be asked for the location to save it to.

### Fixed
- Fixed errors in the key creation process that would sometimes cause wrong data to be read.
- Fixed an error with formatting of egg and met dates.
- Fixed symbols in names not showing up.

### Changed
- Updated to new Electron version again.

### Fixed
- Fixed the updater on Windows and Linux.

### Fixed
- Fixed remote builds (again).

### Changed
- Updated to Electron 0.36.3.

### Fixed
- Fixed a bug that prevented scrolling the dumping output if it overflowed horizontally. Fixes #64.

### Fixed
- Fixed remote builds.

### Changed
- Show a progress bar for a download instead of a spinner.

### Fixed
- Fixed the updater (again).

### Fixed
- Fixed various bugs with the updater.

### Fixed
- Fixed a bug that prevented the `ballName` and `eggLocationName` formatting helpers from working correctly.

### Fixed
- Added the `ballName` formatting helper to properly display ball names. Use this instead of `{{itemName ball}}`.
- Fixed a typo that prevented the app from loading.
- Fixed a CSS bug that prevented the app from displaying properly.
- Format header fields for `ballName` and `ribbons` are now generated.

### Fixed
- Fixed the display of changelog information in an update prompt.

### Added
- A new formatting helper is available: `ribbons`. It returns a list of all ribbons a Pokémon has.
- A new changelog section with an update query.

### Fixed
- Fixes the CSV formatting string. The Defense IV was missing.

releases.name: v0.15.1
releases.body:
### Fixed
- Enable Undo/Redo for KeySAVe running on a Mac

### Added
- Added the ability to break for old style keys if necessary.

### Fixed
- Fixed a bug that prevented new keys from being saved correctly.

### Added
- Added support for old keys from KeySAV2 that do require saving twice.
- Added the ability to upgrade old keys to new keys.

### Changed
- Added entry and exit animations for the multiple tabs.

### Fixed
- Fixed the clear selection buttons in the filter section.

### Added
- Added “eggs only” filter.
- Added species filter.
- Added gender filter.
- Added Hidden Power filter.
- Added nature filter.
- Added ability filter.
- Added “has HA” filter.
- Added “number of perfect IVs” filter.
- Added IV filters.
- Added shininess filter.
- Added “shiny override”.
- Added SV filters.

### Fixed
- You can now open files without extensions on Linux.
- You can now use Cmd+c, Cmd+v and Cmd+x on OS X to Copy/Paste/Cut.

### Fixed
- The updater should now work again.

### Fixed
- You can now open files with no extensions on Windows. (I.e. main files, battle videos, etc.)

_This version is broken._

### Added
- Added support for dumping from RAMSAV and PCData dumps.

### Fixed
- A sensible default header field for the Pokéball is now generated.
- Reddit formatting is fixed to generate proper markdown tables.

### Changed
- The encryption constant is now correctly called that in generated headers.

### Added
- Add formatting options for location names (met location and egg location).

### Fixed
- Fixed a bug with stat calculations with forms that don't have changed base stats that also prevented all Pokémon after the one affected from being dumped.
- Add header defaults for new formatting options.

### Fixed
- The GitHub issues link now opens in the default browser.
- The auto updater works again.

### Changed
- Improve the UI responsiveness while scanning a folder to improve the keys.

### Added
- Add formatting options for actual Pokémon stats.

### Fixed
- An error message that was shown when opening KeySAVe while you are offline.

### Added
- A language selector for the dumping output.
- A formatting option for the Pokémon level.

### Fixed
- A bug that prevented YABD dumps from being opened.

### Fixed
- Fixes the layout of an empty format header texture.
- Fixes the size of dropdown lists.

### Added
- The option to scan all saves in a folder to improve the keys.
- An about tab showing the version number, currently, and more information in the future.

### Changed
- Separate the formatting options from the breaking options.

### Added
- Buttons to create backups of saves and battle videos.

### Added
- A button to copy dumping output to the clipboard.
- A button to save dumping output to the hard drive.
- A button to export dumped pk6 files.

### Changed
- When opening a save, both internal saves will be scanned for better keys.

### Fixed
- Keys are now actually persisted to the drive when you close the application.
- Slots that are just unlocked from the current save are also shown.
- Layout bugs in the options tab.

### Fixed
- A bug with the positioning of the label for the "reset header to default" button.

### Added
- Button to reset the formatting header to a sensible default generated from the format string.
- Formatting option to show OT gender.
- Formatting option to show minimum steps to hatch.
- Formatting option to check for HA.
- Formatting option to show held items.
- Formatting option to show the Gen VI Pentagon.
- Formatting option to show hatched/met date.
- Formatting option to show conditions with a checkmark.
- Formatting option to show an optional shiny mark.
- Formatting option to show a link to the relevant Pokéball image on [/r/svexchange](https://reddit.com/r/svexchange).
- Formatting option to show the region (e.g. Kalos, Hoenn) the country comes from.
- Formatting option to show the country the OT set his 3DS to.
- Formatting option to show forms.
- Formatting option to show markings.

### Fixed
- A bug that would occur when opening two saves after each other.

### Fixed
- Fixed a bug with the auto updating mechanism, that would cause some updates to fail unpredictably.
- Fixed the layout for the auto updater.

### Added
- A formatting option for the game the Pokémon was obtained on, i.e. OR/AS/X/Y/B/W/...

### Fixed
- You can no longer change default formatting options since those changes won't be persisted.

### Changed
- Bundled formatting options can no longer be deleted.

### Added
- Added an option to clone a formatting option. Useful to change the builtin ones.
- Added a loading screen while downloading updates to lock the UI and inform the user of what is going on.

It is **recommended** you delete your config file in `~/Documents/KeySAVe/config.json` after your update to this version.

### Added
- An automatic update mechanism. If a new release is found you will be prompted to download it upon application start.
- You can now generate actual HTML in your templates that will be rendered.
- Linux builds (both 32 and 64-bit).

### Fixed
- A bug that could occur when viewing files with Pokémon with the same PID (cloned ones).

releases.name: v0.3.1
releases.body: - Fixes #1. If keys are copied into the data folder after the app is opened, they are now found and used.

releases.name: KeySAVe v0.3.0
releases.body:
- Removed dump buttons from UI. Why would you want to open a file and not look at what's inside?
- Add format headers.
- Ship a CSV format string. If you want to use the new defaults, please delete ~/Documents/KeySAVe/config.json.
- Dynamically reformat outputs if format string is changed in the options.

releases.name: KeySAVe v0.2.1
releases.body: Adapted formatting options to what comes with standard KeySAV2.

releases.name: KeySAVe
releases.body: You can now add, remove and rename formatting options at will. They will be persisted to the file system, as well as the currently selected formatting option. Also language tags are available for formatting.

releases.name: KeySAVe
releases.body: This version was tested a fair bit, fixes all significant bugs and persists changes to formatting options to a config file.
